1
00:00:02,682 --> 00:00:04,409
Seo Ju Ho?

2
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:34,900
Is this...

3
00:00:46,373 --> 00:00:49,743
[Best Mistake]

4
00:00:52,032 --> 00:00:55,090
It should be here somewhere.

5
00:00:56,168 --> 00:00:58,310
Darn...

6
00:00:59,461 --> 00:01:01,583
This has also gone bad.

7
00:01:04,062 --> 00:01:07,076
Please put the laundry in the laundry bin.

8
00:01:07,076 --> 00:01:09,401
What is this?

9
00:01:09,401 --> 00:01:11,987
Please. I tried to put it away.

10
00:01:11,987 --> 00:01:15,276
- And what is this?
- Please.

11
00:01:16,837 --> 00:01:18,629
Look at this.

12
00:01:18,629 --> 00:01:20,883
It's dangerous this way.

13
00:01:20,883 --> 00:01:22,739
There is dust in between...

14
00:01:22,739 --> 00:01:24,924
It's usually not like this.

15
00:01:24,924 --> 00:01:28,040
I was charging my phone just now and left it this way.

16
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,887
For God's sake.

17
00:01:32,108 --> 00:01:34,960
Hey! Can't you throw away what you ate right away?

18
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,571
I will!

19
00:01:36,595 --> 00:01:38,995
I was going to.

20
00:01:40,554 --> 00:01:42,477
Hold on.

21
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:45,955
This is my house. Why am I being conscious?

22
00:01:45,955 --> 00:01:49,158
Hey, you... Why are you acting like the owner here?

23
00:01:49,158 --> 00:01:50,928
What did I do?

24
00:01:50,977 --> 00:01:53,569
Weren't you going to that tattoo thing?

25
00:01:53,569 --> 00:01:56,667
Why are you still here?

26
00:01:56,711 --> 00:01:58,730
I'm going later.

27
00:02:03,712 --> 00:02:05,626
Is something wrong?

28
00:02:05,644 --> 00:02:08,918
Why are you so down?

29
00:02:08,918 --> 00:02:11,054
Nothing's wrong.

30
00:02:11,069 --> 00:02:15,119
Your face says it all. What is it?

31
00:02:19,832 --> 00:02:21,593
Seol was...

32
00:02:21,593 --> 00:02:25,142
Yu Seol? What about her?

33
00:02:27,118 --> 00:02:28,969
She...

34
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:39,439
What? When did you come? You didn't say anything.

35
00:02:41,829 --> 00:02:43,647
Seo Ju Ho?

36
00:02:45,112 --> 00:02:48,838
Who was that guy?

37
00:02:48,838 --> 00:02:52,627
- Is it your new boyfriend?
- What?

38
00:02:52,627 --> 00:02:55,602
Well, you said you would wait for me to come back.

39
00:02:55,602 --> 00:02:59,021
You wanted me to give this back to you

40
00:02:59,021 --> 00:03:01,624
when you returned to Korea.

41
00:03:01,624 --> 00:03:05,533
- How could you... just like that...
- Stop assuming things.

42
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:07,563
What about you?

43
00:03:07,563 --> 00:03:12,626
When did you come to Korea? You never told me.

44
00:03:12,626 --> 00:03:15,196
It's been a few days.

45
00:03:15,196 --> 00:03:18,981
I wanted to come in front of you and surprise you, so I didn't say anything.

46
00:03:18,981 --> 00:03:20,978
What?

47
00:03:20,978 --> 00:03:25,085
Then who is that guy? Does he like you?

48
00:03:25,085 --> 00:03:28,722
Has he been following you? Is that it?

49
00:03:30,124 --> 00:03:32,496
Seo Ju Ho.

50
00:03:32,496 --> 00:03:35,430
You don't think about me, do you?

51
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:36,610
What?

52
00:03:36,616 --> 00:03:39,691
You leave suddenly then come back like this.

53
00:03:39,691 --> 00:03:41,776
How can you be so selfish all the time?

54
00:03:41,776 --> 00:03:42,965
Seol...

55
00:03:42,965 --> 00:03:45,119
You always think only of yourself

56
00:03:45,119 --> 00:03:49,001
I am not in your priority, am I?

57
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:56,742
Sure...

58
00:03:56,742 --> 00:03:58,994
I said I would wait,

59
00:03:58,994 --> 00:04:02,487
but... not anymore.

60
00:04:02,487 --> 00:04:05,918
From now on, you wait for me.

61
00:04:05,918 --> 00:04:10,824
Just like I did for you. You have a crush on me.

62
00:04:18,188 --> 00:04:22,533
Am I... dumped?

63
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:25,321
You shouldn't have been so hard to get in high school.

64
00:04:25,321 --> 00:04:29,107
Back then... It's...

65
00:04:34,815 --> 00:04:37,356
What are you looking for since earlier?

66
00:04:37,356 --> 00:04:40,622
There should be at least one here somewhere.

67
00:04:40,622 --> 00:04:45,114
What is it? Tell me what you're looking for, and I'll...

68
00:04:47,752 --> 00:04:50,166
Found it.

69
00:04:56,121 --> 00:04:58,242
Shall I start?

70
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:06,600
♫ I'm just in another world, being cool ♫

71
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:09,600
♫ Being myself ♫

72
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:14,400
♫ In a different dimension I'm having fun ♫

73
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,098
[Department of Business Administration]

74
00:05:30,138 --> 00:05:32,715
I'm going crazy.

75
00:05:32,715 --> 00:05:34,493
Assistant?

76
00:05:34,493 --> 00:05:37,900
- Oh? Yes... What is it?
- Is something the matter?

77
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:41,357
It's about scholarship documents. I should hand them in by today.

78
00:05:41,357 --> 00:05:43,955
And I forgot to get the signatures.

79
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:53,128
Why isn't Yeon Du answering the phone?

80
00:05:53,128 --> 00:05:56,081
She didn't even have class today.

81
00:05:56,110 --> 00:05:59,515
- Kim Yeon Du?
- Yes.

82
00:05:59,515 --> 00:06:03,959
This Do Ye Seok! He knows where Yeon Du lives.

83
00:06:03,959 --> 00:06:05,657
What?

84
00:06:05,657 --> 00:06:08,814
You go get it, okay? That will solve it.

85
00:06:08,814 --> 00:06:11,132
Hey, why should I get it?

86
00:06:11,132 --> 00:06:15,317
Here, Ye Seok. Here at the bottom please get the signature.

87
00:06:15,317 --> 00:06:20,372
As you know, as a teacher's assistant, I can't leave my seat.

88
00:06:20,372 --> 00:06:22,552
Please, I beg you, Ye Seok.

89
00:06:27,121 --> 00:06:29,964
- But still...
- Will you do it?

90
00:06:29,964 --> 00:06:32,934
I knew it! I'll buy you a meal sometime.

91
00:06:32,934 --> 00:06:34,940
They have great food at the school cafeteria.

92
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:38,750
♫ I keep thinking of you ♫

93
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:42,498
♫ I keep not forgetting you ♫

94
00:06:42,498 --> 00:06:44,910
Oh? Who could it be?

95
00:06:44,910 --> 00:06:47,780
♫ My heart keeps skipping a beat ♫

96
00:06:47,796 --> 00:06:50,150
Who is it?

97
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:53,950
♫ I'm missing you so much ♫

98
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:55,971
Senior!

99
00:06:55,971 --> 00:06:59,823
Yes. The TA sent me...

100
00:07:02,764 --> 00:07:04,780
Are you Squirtle?

101
00:07:04,780 --> 00:07:07,340
[Hwayang High School 3-3]
[Squirtle]

102
00:07:08,786 --> 00:07:10,615
Hold on.

103
00:07:13,773 --> 00:07:17,143
Yes, TA. I just sent you the photo of the document.

104
00:07:17,143 --> 00:07:20,105
Okay, thank you.

105
00:07:20,105 --> 00:07:22,033
- Is it all good?
- Yes.

106
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:25,611
If you hadn't done it, I wouldn't have received the scholarship.

107
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:27,945
Then I'll be off now.

108
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,147
Oh, It fell again.

109
00:07:33,147 --> 00:07:36,547
Seol drew it for me.

110
00:07:36,547 --> 00:07:40,165
Should I... help you?

111
00:07:44,364 --> 00:07:47,875
I can hammer a nail by myself.

112
00:07:55,729 --> 00:07:58,475
Why isn't it working?

113
00:07:58,475 --> 00:08:00,980
I think it's in the wrong direction.

114
00:08:01,049 --> 00:08:03,086
Let me take a look.

115
00:08:13,906 --> 00:08:15,725
Nail.

116
00:08:23,843 --> 00:08:25,749
Here.

117
00:08:27,498 --> 00:08:30,865
Oh? Yes.

118
00:08:37,031 --> 00:08:40,476
Are you all right? Did you hammer on your finger?

119
00:08:40,476 --> 00:08:42,466
No, I didn't.

120
00:08:42,466 --> 00:08:45,421
I think you did. Let me see. Did you get hurt bad?

121
00:08:45,421 --> 00:08:48,656
No, I really didn't. It doesn't hurt at all.

122
00:08:48,656 --> 00:08:50,391
What?

123
00:08:50,391 --> 00:08:54,489
What I mean is... It slightly...

124
00:08:54,489 --> 00:08:56,287
brushed off.

125
00:08:58,593 --> 00:09:01,596
Wow, it doesn't hurt one bit.

126
00:09:03,161 --> 00:09:04,769
It's true.

127
00:09:06,394 --> 00:09:09,872
Senior Ye Seok, let me do it.

128
00:09:26,368 --> 00:09:29,920
- So I get to have it upwards like this, right?
- Yes.

129
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,868
You're doing great.

130
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:40,020
Does it hurt a lot?

131
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:42,156
Come here.

132
00:09:47,453 --> 00:09:51,000
Senior Ye Seok, thank you for today.

133
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,811
You also helped me with the picture.

134
00:09:56,755 --> 00:10:00,738
No need to thank me. It was nothing.

135
00:10:17,461 --> 00:10:20,078
Was it you?

136
00:10:20,078 --> 00:10:22,209
Her boyfriend?

137
00:10:27,632 --> 00:10:30,895
- Then I'll see you at school tomorrow.
- Okay.

138
00:10:30,895 --> 00:10:33,200
Go home safely.

139
00:10:40,741 --> 00:10:42,562
Kim Yeon Du!

140
00:10:47,408 --> 00:10:51,127
Who is that? What's he doing here?

141
00:10:51,127 --> 00:10:55,644
He's a senior at school. He came by for a reason.

142
00:10:55,644 --> 00:10:59,315
But why do I have to tell you this?

143
00:10:59,315 --> 00:11:01,145
- What?
- Why are you here?

144
00:11:01,169 --> 00:11:05,367
- I told you not to come like this...
- Here.

145
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:07,261
Your hairband.

146
00:11:12,930 --> 00:11:15,625
Did you come to return this?

147
00:11:15,625 --> 00:11:19,236
You could've just thrown it away.

148
00:11:19,236 --> 00:11:22,332
- It's an excuse.
- What?

149
00:11:22,332 --> 00:11:24,942
An excuse to come see you.

150
00:11:26,117 --> 00:11:29,160
I really missed you.

151
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:31,559
I've got more,

152
00:11:31,559 --> 00:11:34,787
but I just brought you this today.

153
00:11:34,787 --> 00:11:39,455
If I give back all at once, I have no excuse to come see you.

154
00:11:41,044 --> 00:11:44,484
- So I'll return them one at a time.
- You don't need to. I...

155
00:11:44,484 --> 00:11:47,631
When I see you once, twice, and three times like that,

156
00:11:47,631 --> 00:11:50,909
and when you feel better about us,

157
00:11:50,909 --> 00:11:53,520
let's start going out again.

158
00:11:54,922 --> 00:11:57,963
I'll be waiting until that time.

159
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:01,689
No.

160
00:12:01,689 --> 00:12:03,725
That won't happen.

161
00:12:03,725 --> 00:12:06,593
I'm all done.

162
00:12:06,593 --> 00:12:09,136
So don't wait anymore.

163
00:12:09,136 --> 00:12:11,693
Don't come like this, either.

164
00:13:13,062 --> 00:13:14,834
It's all because of you.

165
00:13:14,834 --> 00:13:17,749
- Hyeon Ho...
- Let me go!

166
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:12,800
Ah Ra? Ah Ra!

167
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,740
What are you doing here, Ji Seong?

168
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:19,700
What do you mean? This is the academy where I study.

169
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:23,224
Is that so? I had no idea.

170
00:14:23,224 --> 00:14:26,461
What about you, Ah Ra? What brings you here?

171
00:14:26,461 --> 00:14:28,140
Me?

172
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,800
I was meeting a friend at the 2nd floor,

173
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:36,000
and now I'm on my way home. On the way home.

174
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,500
I see.

175
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:43,500
Then... it's totally a coincidence.

176
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:47,148
I know. I'm happy to see you coincidently.

177
00:14:47,148 --> 00:14:50,400
- Shall we have a meal together?
- Meal?

178
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:56,800
I need to go to the bookstore now.

179
00:14:56,800 --> 00:15:00,100
Bookstore? That's great!

180
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:03,500
I was also on my way to the bookstore.

181
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:08,132
Let's go to the bookstore, then have a meal.

182
00:15:08,132 --> 00:15:12,442
- But didn't you say you're meeting your friend—
- Oh, it just got canceled.

183
00:15:12,442 --> 00:15:14,300
Where is the bookstore?

184
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:16,600
Is it this way? Let's go.

185
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,900
Oh... Okay, let's go.

186
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:26,400
I can buy these myself.

187
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,500
It's okay.

188
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:31,700
This is a present for you, Ji Seong.

189
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:38,900
It's Happy Money. You're giving me this?

190
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:44,664
When you study, you need to purchase a lot of workbooks or reference books, like today.

191
00:15:44,664 --> 00:15:47,700
So use this Happy Money.

192
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,207
Ah Ra.

193
00:15:49,207 --> 00:15:52,040
Of course, you can use it for playing games and shopping.

194
00:15:52,064 --> 00:15:54,455
But studying is your main concern for now,

195
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:58,300
so use it only to buy books, okay?

196
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:04,000
Okay. I will really use it to buy books.

197
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,600
Thanks, Ah Ra.

198
00:16:06,604 --> 00:16:08,582
Since you gave me the present,

199
00:16:08,582 --> 00:16:12,300
I will buy you the tteokbokki today.

200
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:15,100
Please take the order, Auntie!

201
00:16:20,732 --> 00:16:22,879
Thank you.

202
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,300
It's so spicy.

203
00:16:31,336 --> 00:16:34,566
I told you to get the mild one. You're so stubborn.

204
00:16:34,566 --> 00:16:36,928
Spicy food gives you a sense of pain...

205
00:16:36,928 --> 00:16:41,000
And it produces endorphin in your brain?

206
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,000
I know.

207
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:47,103
Is someone bullying you?

208
00:16:47,103 --> 00:16:50,218
There's someone worse than Noh Shin Wu.

209
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,900
That's not good.

210
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:15,800
Noh Shin Wu, don't be obvious but just turn around slowly.

211
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:26,000
Isn't that President Shin Da On? He's with a girl.

212
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,937
No, he's not. I thought it was him at first.

213
00:17:28,937 --> 00:17:31,600
But he's just a lookalike.

214
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:37,900
Wow. He even smiles the same way.

215
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,900
I'm jealous, Woo Tae Gyeong.

216
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:52,600
When I look at him again, President Shin Da On seems more handsome.

217
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,300
Do you want to die?

218
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:58,300
I'm joking.

219
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:01,400
Who's better than you, Noh Shin Wu?

220
00:18:07,718 --> 00:18:09,861
Enjoy your food, Ah Ra.

221
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:12,200
Thanks, Ji Seong.

222
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,900
Give me your dish, let me serve you tteokbokki.

223
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:20,800
- Ouch, it's hot!
- Ah Ra!

224
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,900
Did you get burnt? Are you alright?

225
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:27,000
- Did it splash on you?
- No.

226
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,600
It must have been hot.

227
00:18:38,468 --> 00:18:40,360
- Are you finished?
- Yes.

228
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:43,766
If it weren't for your help, I wouldn't have finished it by today.

229
00:18:43,766 --> 00:18:46,200
- Thank you so much.
- No need.

230
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:50,100
I took the class in my freshman year, so I just helped you out.

231
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:57,100
By the way, your bag... It's so pretty.

232
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:59,700
And it goes well with you.

233
00:18:59,742 --> 00:19:02,829
Really? Thanks.

234
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:07,100
Now I should look for some photos.

235
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:10,000
Photos? What kind of photos?

236
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,000
Oh, I recently joined an intercollegiate club.

237
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:16,600
It's a photography club so I want to study in advance.

238
00:19:16,606 --> 00:19:18,996
Do they do activities with people from different colleges, don't they?

239
00:19:18,996 --> 00:19:22,500
Yes, but there are a lot of students from our school this time.

240
00:19:22,559 --> 00:19:25,894
The president is Senior Dae Yeong from our department.

241
00:19:25,894 --> 00:19:30,200
Some of my friends are also joining.

242
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:32,681
Oh... And...

243
00:19:32,681 --> 00:19:35,960
Right, Senior Ye Seok is also joining—

244
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:38,480
Yes.

245
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,602
Ye Seok?

246
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:51,600
What's that expression? Someone might think you're telling me off.

247
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:54,300
Pardon?

248
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:56,600
Did Ye Seok tell you not to tell me?

249
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:59,300
No. I just heard it, too.

250
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:02,500
Senior Dae Yeong told me that.

251
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:12,600
Is Do Ye Seok joining a club?

252
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:16,300
Thank you for the meal.

253
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:24,100
It was better in school.

254
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:26,900
Everything was good except for the studies.

255
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:31,100
I will surely go to college with you guys.

256
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:33,700
There won't be a third time.

257
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:36,900
You will get in to a college for sure, Ji Seong.

258
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,700
You're studying so hard like this.

259
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:42,575
Thanks, Ah Ra.

260
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,900
I will carry this for you.

261
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:49,200
No, I can do it myself.

262
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:52,300
Your study hands might get injured.

263
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:54,600
Let me carry them.

264
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:01,100
Ah Ra, you hurt your hand just now.

265
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:04,000
Therefore, let me do it.

266
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:07,600
No, I'm really fine.

267
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,431
I'm not.

268
00:21:14,117 --> 00:21:17,228
Ji Seong, I don't want to disturb your study

269
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:20,191
and I'm patiently waiting like this.

270
00:21:20,191 --> 00:21:24,259
So think of me and do well on the exam, okay?

271
00:21:24,259 --> 00:21:28,732
When you're done with the exam, I'll grant you a wish.

272
00:21:28,732 --> 00:21:31,500
A wish? What wish?

273
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:34,500
What you want the most, Ji Seong.

274
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,100
By chance?

275
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:44,300
A PlayStation?

276
00:21:45,528 --> 00:21:50,539
But that is too expensive. She doesn't have to be that nice.

277
00:21:50,539 --> 00:21:52,700
Ah Ra!

278
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,800
[Intercollegiate Photo Club Moment]
[New Members Orientation]

279
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:03,300
Did Senior Dae Yeong ask you to join as well?

280
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:05,300
He talked me in, too.

281
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:08,900
He said it's really fun and that he'll be really nice.

282
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:12,100
He said the same thing to you, right?

283
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,900
Oh... Well...

284
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:19,800
I'm pleased to be joining. Taking photos seems fun.

285
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:23,900
By the way, Yeon Du.

286
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:28,700
Is it because you're a Squirtle, you're eating Squirtle Chips?

287
00:22:29,900 --> 00:22:31,700
N-No.

288
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:37,183
I just like chocolate-flavored chips.

289
00:22:37,183 --> 00:22:40,073
Okay. Squirtle Chips.

290
00:22:40,073 --> 00:22:43,000
Stop making fun.

291
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:46,300
Try one. It's so tasty.

292
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:48,500
Is it that tasty?

293
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:03,200
Hello. I'm a new member, Ji Hyeon Ho.

294
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:25,300
Sorry for being late.

295
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:44,700
[Best Mistake 3]

296
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:48,600
[A few hours ago]

297
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:55,500
What's the bandage for? How did you get hurt?

298
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:02,530
Oh... I just... I just got hurt.

299
00:24:02,530 --> 00:24:04,700
While doing something.

300
00:24:04,700 --> 00:24:08,047
Anyway, you're quite careless.

301
00:24:08,047 --> 00:24:10,020
Bandag—

302
00:24:10,020 --> 00:24:13,300
What's with the childish bandage?

303
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:15,000
Well...

304
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,500
It hurts.

305
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:26,430
Look who's talking... What happened to you?

306
00:24:26,430 --> 00:24:29,530
Why did you get hurt?

307
00:24:29,530 --> 00:24:34,600
I... I just... I just... got hurt somehow.

308
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,900
- Let's hurry up.
- Yeah, okay.

309
00:24:41,289 --> 00:24:44,308
When four 20 year olds visit you get a combo fries for free?

310
00:24:44,308 --> 00:24:48,300
When four 20 year olds visit, you get all this for free!

311
00:24:56,560 --> 00:25:01,300
♫ The two of us that seems 100 percent close and perfect ♫

312
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:04,000
Are you going to keep on following me and making me uncomfortable?

313
00:25:04,055 --> 00:25:06,704
- Why are you so uncomfortable?
- Because—

314
00:25:06,704 --> 00:25:08,400
Seol, are you okay?

315
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:10,700
Seo Ju Ho might just leave again.

316
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:12,563
Do you believe in fate?

317
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:15,200
Running into you like this is a bit amazing.

318
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:17,700
They're not just a senior and a junior.

319
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:20,000
You still like Kim Yeon Du, don't you?

320
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:22,190
What are you scheming?

321
00:25:22,190 --> 00:25:27,740
♫ we still cross the lines ♫

322
00:25:27,740 --> 00:25:30,120
